					Re: The Lost Amulet
				</h2>
				

						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1755376">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							That is an excellent first pass; simple and direct. It conveys the beginnings of a tale well enough that I want to read more, which is the point of all introductions.<br />
<br />
Two things: The first line should be a real grabber, but reads flat.<br />
<br />
Second: Beware the trap of the wise and capable protagonist. Remember that his growth is ultimately what the reader expects to experience vicariously, through your story. Make sure to leave yourself room to stretch him out a bit.<br />
<br />
Good stuff, Ali!
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
